22 statute to be punishable as a felony; provided further, that
23 municipalities.
24
ENGR. S. B. NO. 1775 Page 5

1 6. Municipalities having a municipal court not of record may
2 enact ordinances prescribing maximum fines of One Thousand Dollars
3 ($1,000.00) and costs or imprisonment not exceeding ninety (90) days
4 or both such fine and imprisonment for violations of municipal
5 ordinances regulating the pretreatment of wastewater and regulating
6 stormwater discharges. If imprisonment is available for the
7 offense, then that person charged shall have a right to a jury
8 trial.
9 D. Municipalities having both municipal criminal courts of
10 record and municipal courts not of record may enact ordinances,
11 within the authority of this section, for each court.
12 E. No municipality may levy a fine or deferral fee in lieu of a
13 fine of over Fifty Dollars ($50.00) until it has compiled and
14 published its penal ordinances as required in Sections 14-109 and
15 14-110 of this title.
16 F. No municipality may levy a fine of more than Ten Dollars
17 ($10.00) nor court costs of more than Fifteen Dollars ($15.00) for
18 exceeding the posted speed limit by no more than ten (10) miles per
19 hour upon any portion of the National System of Interstate and
20 Defense Highways, federal-aid primary highways, and or the state
21 highway system which are is located on the outskirts of any
22 municipality as determined in Section 2-117 of Title 47 of the
23 Oklahoma Statutes.
24
ENGR. S. B. NO. 1775 Page 6

1 G. If any fine or deferral fee in lieu of a fine, as stated in
2 a municipal ordinance, or any other fine or fee schedule adopted by
3 a municipality, exceeds the maximum amount authorized by this
4 section or other applicable statutes for the same offense, the
5 amount is void and unenforceable to the extent of the excess amount
6 and shall be deemed reformed and reduced by operation of law to the
7 maximum lawful amount.
8 SECTION 2. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
9 of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
10 declared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
11 be in full force from and after its passage and approval.
12 Passed the Senate the 26th day of March, 2026.
